== Portuguese ==
=== Verb ===
'''tomar'''
# (''transitive'') to [[take]] (something);
#: "''Fui ao banco '''tomar''' meu dinheiro.''" - I went to the bank to take my money.
# (''transitive'') to [[steal]] (something);
#: "''O ladrão '''tomou''' todo o meu dinheiro.''" - The thief have stolen all my money.
# (''transitive'') to consider that something or someone (direct object) is other thing or other one (''[[por]]'');
#: "''Eu '''tomei''' a Maria por corrupta.''" - I thought Mary were corrupt.
# (''transitive'') to [[drink]];
#: "''Eu '''tomei''' suco.''" - I drank juice.
# (''intransitive'') to [[consume]] [[alcoholic]] [[beverage]]s;
#: "''Ele '''toma''' muito, durante os finais de semana.''" - He drinks a lot, on weekends.
# (''intransitive, vulgar'') to [[be]] [[fucked]];

